<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,152,812]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,337,749,775]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honour of the late Michael Shaffer, who contributed profoundly to the research of Pyraloidea for more than 
<number box="[630,659,786,812]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" value="50.0">50</number>
years in the Natural History Museum (
<collectionCode box="[1117,1211,786,812]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">BMNH</collectionCode>
), London.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
